    {
      "id": "port-contract-root",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Overview",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": 10,
        "y": -320
      },
      "width": 470,
      "height": 270,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Port Contract\n\n**Authority:** Normative host-owned boundary\n\nThis contract defines what a Twilite port means, what it may expose, and how host-owned authority is filtered before navigation, view consumption, bridging, or runtime behavior crosses a graph boundary.\n\nPorts are semantic APIs, not just connection dots. Direction is semantic, authority is explicit, and effective capability may stay the same or downgrade at the boundary.\n\nThis graph is the contract.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "markdown",
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "port-contract-declaration"
        },
        "_placement": {
