    {
      "id": "port-contract-required",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Required Structure",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": -560,
        "y": 40
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 300,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Required Structure\n\nEvery normative port contract MUST declare:\n\n- a stable port id\n- declared direction: `input | output | bidirectional`\n- an explicit authority ladder entry on the host port instance\n- semantic meaning that explains why the port exists\n- compatibility rules that define what may connect\n- validation behavior for incompatible or over-authorized requests\n\nHost authority is the starting point. Target richness never upgrades authority by itself.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "markdown",
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "port-contract-declaration"
        },
        "_placement": {
