    {
      "id": "port-contract-validation",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Validation",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": 940,
        "y": 40
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 320,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Validation\n\nResolve a port boundary in five passes:\n\n1. Read the host port authority.\n2. Read the target graph exposure and requested surface.\n3. Check semantic compatibility, multiplicity, and wildcard policy.\n4. Apply any local downgrade or refusal policy.\n5. Only allow runtime behavior if the effective authority is `runtime` and the target surface explicitly supports it.\n\nValidation must be deterministic and portable.",
