    {
      "id": "port-contract-authority-ladder",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Authority Ladder",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": -320,
        "y": 470
      },
      "width": 440,
      "height": 320,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Authority Ladder\n\nThe host port instance declares authority:\n\n- `navigate`: open the target without consuming its surface\n- `consume-view`: read a passive exposed surface\n- `bridge`: grant class, artifact, or capability import behavior\n- `runtime`: allow explicitly-declared runtime-capable surfaces\n\nNew ports default to `navigate`. Effective authority may stay the same or downgrade across a boundary. It may never silently increase.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "markdown",
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "port-contract-declaration"
        },
        "_placement": {
