    {
      "id": "port-contract-compatibility",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Compatibility",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": 180,
        "y": 470
      },
      "width": 440,
      "height": 320,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Compatibility\n\nCompatibility is semantic, not cosmetic.\n\n- Direction describes meaning flow, not screen position.\n- Semantic types are conceptual compatibility declarations, not programming-language types.\n- Multiplicity constrains how many compatible edges may exist without ambiguity.\n- Wildcard behavior must be explicit.\n\nIf misuse does not make something false, the meaning is probably underdeclared.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "markdown",
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "port-contract-declaration"
