    {
      "id": "port-contract-agent-rules",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Agent Rules",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": 1180,
        "y": 470
      },
      "width": 440,
      "height": 300,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Agent Rules\n\nAgents may author or edit ports, but they MUST:\n\n- preserve host-owned authority\n- declare semantic meaning before wiring behavior\n- avoid inferring capability from view richness\n- keep wildcard and compatibility policy explicit\n- treat consumed views as passive unless `runtime` is both allowed and declared\n\nIf the contract is unclear, agents should ask or downgrade.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "markdown",
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "port-contract-declaration"
        },
        "_placement": {
